CBS Corp. (CBS)  said it won the ratings
race for the 2011-2012 prime-time TV season, averaging 11.7
million viewers a night and leading the second-place finisher,
Fox, by the largest margin in 23 years.  The CBS network, based in  New York , said it won the ratings
for the ninth time in the past 10 years, according to an e-
mailed statement today. The network came in second place to  News
